column1: NGR is a place called Lluest SW of Gathbibio. The 1868 British Rainfall report has a map that implies the gauge is about 50deg 40' N and 3deg 46' W, which is consistent with the NGR used.
Combined readings are Oct to Dec 1866 = 18.33?, Jan to Mar 1867 = 16.4, Aug - Sep 1867 = 84, Oct - Dec 1867 = 14.8, Feb- Mar 18881 =11.9 and Oct - Nov = 9.8
